00012 /*
00013  * The number of bytes in an ethernet (MAC) address.
00014  */
00015 #define ETHER_ADDR_LEN          6
00016 
00017 /*
00018  * The number of bytes in the type field.
00019  */
00020 #define ETHER_TYPE_LEN          2
00021 
00022 /*
00023  * The number of bytes in the trailing CRC field.
00024  */
00025 #define ETHER_CRC_LEN           4
00026 
00027 /*
00028  * Mbuf adjust factor to force 32-bit alignment of IP header.
00029  * Drivers should do m_adj(m, ETHER_ALIGN) when setting up a
00030  * receive so the upper layers get the IP header properly aligned
00031  * past the 14-byte Ethernet header.
00032  */
00033 #define ETHER_ALIGN             2
00034 
00035 /*
00036  * The length of the combined header.
00037  */
00038 #define ETHER_HDR_LEN           (ETHER_ADDR_LEN*2+ETHER_TYPE_LEN)
00039 
00040 /*
00041  * The minimum packet length.
00042  */
00043 #define ETHER_MIN_LEN           64
00044 
00045 /*
00046  * The maximum packet length.
00047  */
00048 #define ETHER_MAX_LEN           1518
00049 
00050 /*
00051  * A macro to validate a length with
00052  */
00053 #define ETHER_IS_VALID_LEN(foo) \
00054         ((foo) >= ETHER_MIN_LEN && (foo) <= ETHER_MAX_LEN)
00055 
00056 /*
00057  * Ethernet CRC32 polynomials (big- and little-endian verions).
00058  */
00059 #define ETHER_CRC_POLY_LE       0xedb88320
00060 #define ETHER_CRC_POLY_BE       0x04c11db6

00062 /*
00063  * Structure of a 10Mb/s Ethernet header.
00064  */
00065 struct  ether_header {
00066         u_char  ether_dhost[ETHER_ADDR_LEN];
00067         u_char  ether_shost[ETHER_ADDR_LEN];
00068         u_short ether_type;
00069 };

00071 /*
00072  * Structure of a 48-bit Ethernet address.
00073  */
00074 struct  ether_addr {

00076 };
